        \brief Run the model returning results in an Ort allocated vector. Wraps OrtApi::Run The caller provides a list of inputs and a list of the desired outputs to return. See the output logs for more information on warnings/errors that occur while processing the model. Common errors are.. (TODO)

        run_options - [in]

        input_count - [in] Number of inputs (the size of the input_names & input_values arrays)

      • RunAsync

        public void RunAsync(@Const @ByRef
                     RunOptions run_options,
                     @Cast(value="const char*const*")
                     PointerPointer input_names,
                     @Const
                     Value input_values,
                     @Cast(value="size_t")
                     long input_count,
                     @Cast(value="const char*const*")
                     PointerPointer output_names,
                     Value output_values,
                     @Cast(value="size_t")
                     long output_count,
                     RunAsyncCallbackFn callback,
                     Pointer user_data)
        \brief Run the model asynchronously in a thread owned by intra op thread pool Wraps OrtApi::RunAsync
        Parameters:
        run_options - [in]
        input_names - [in] Array of null terminated UTF8 encoded strings of the input names
        input_values - [in] Array of Value objects of length input_count
        input_count - [in] Number of elements in the input_names and inputs arrays
        output_names - [in] Array of null terminated UTF8 encoded strings of the output names
        output_values - [out] Array of provided Values to be filled with outputs. On calling RunAsync, output_values[i] could either be initialized by a null pointer or a preallocated OrtValue*. Later, on invoking the callback, each output_values[i] of null will be filled with an OrtValue* allocated by onnxruntime. Then, an OrtValue** pointer will be casted from output_values, and pass to the callback. NOTE: it is customer's duty to finally release output_values and each of its member, regardless of whether the member (Ort::Value) is allocated by onnxruntime or preallocated by the customer.
        output_count - [in] Number of elements in the output_names and outputs array
        callback - [in] Callback function on model run completion
        user_data - [in] User data that pass back to the callback
